column873: business_description:"QQQ is one of the best established and typically one of the most actively traded ETFs in the world. Often referred to as the triple Qs
column874: it's also one of the most unusual. The product is one of a few ETFs structured as a unit investment trust. Per the rules of its index
column875: the fund only invests in nonfinancial stocks listed on NASDAQ
column876: and effectively ignores other sectors too
column877: causing it to skew massively away from a broad-based large-cap portfolio. QQQ has huge tech exposure
column878: but it is not a 'tech fund' in the pure sense either. The fund's arcane weighting rules further distance it from anything close to plain vanilla large-cap or pure-play tech coverage. The ETF is much more concentrated in its top holdings and is more volatile than our vanilla large-cap benchmark. Still
column879: the fund has huge name recognition for the underlying index
column881: QQQ delivers a quirky but wildly popular mash-up of tech
column882: growth and large-cap exposure. The fund and index are rebalanced quarterly and reconstituted annually."
